                                   16701     212.     *         parameter area @IORB which was passed from GSTINTF

                                   23627    1392.     *  IF THE HSPACE KEYWORD WAS SPECIFIED IN THE ORVYL INIT PARAMETERS,
                                   23628    1393.     *  THIS CODE CONVERTS A PAGE OR SWAP OPERATION INTO A HIPERSPACE
                                   23629    1394.     *  REQUEST.  IN THIS ROUTINE WHEN A PAGE OR SWAP CONTROL BLOCK (DDB)
                                   23630    1395.     *  IS ALLOCATED, A CORRESPONDING HIPERSPACE CONTROL BLOCK (HDB) IS
                                   23631    1396.     *  CREATED.  THE HDB IS CHAINED TO THE DDB AND VICE VERSA.
                                   23632    1397.     *
                                   23633    1398.     *  THE MAXSIZE SUBPARAMETER OR A DEFAULT HAS BEEN PLACED INTO IOCTHSIZ
                                   23634    1399.     *  AT IOSINIT. IF A LIMIT TO THE NUMBER OF PAGE OR SWAP DATASETS TO
                                   23635    1400.     *  SIMULATE WAS ALSO SPECIFIED, THESE LIMITS WILL BE IN IOCTPGLM OR
                                   23636    1401.     *  IOCTSWLM.

                                   24201    1504.     *
                                   24202    1505.     *  New for Hiperspace support
                                   24203    1506.     *
                                   24204    1507.     *  IF THE DDB POINTS TO AN HDB WHICH POINTS BACK TO THE DDB, THIS
                                   24205    1508.     *  REPRESENTS A PAGE/SWAP REQUEST WHICH HAS BEEN CONVERTED TO USE
                                   24206    1509.     *  HIPERSPACE SERVICES.  FOR PAGE AND SWAP READ OR WRITE REQUESTS,
                                   24207    1510.     *  WE USE THE HIPERSPACE DRIVERS IN PLACE OF THE PAGE/SWAP DRIVERS.
                                   24208    1511.     *  THERE IS NO HIPERSPACE EQUIVALENT FOR A PAGE RESET SO AN IMMEDIATE
                                   24209    1512.     *  GOOD RETURN CODE IS FAKED OUT.  REAL PAGE AND SWAP OPEN AND CLOSE
                                   24210    1513.     *  REQUESTS ARE PERFORMED BECAUSE THE ORVYL GUEST CALLER EXPECTS SOME
                                   24211    1514.     *  DSCB INFO TO BE PASSED BACK IN #PFINFO.  HOWEVER, A HIPERSPACE
                                   24212    1515.     *  OPEN IS DONE WITH THE FIRST I/O REQUEST SIMULATED.
                                   24213    1516.     *
 USING  #IOCOM,R6                  24214    1517.              WITH  (#IOCOM,RX)

                                   24234    1519.   C HDBSRCH  IF    ('CLC COMDBID(4),=C"DDB "',EQ), DO WE HAVE A DDB?

0                                  35802             =*  The page list pointed to by #HSPLIST follows.
                                   35803             =*  The first entry is a pointer to the next list
                                   35804             =*  which is zero for the last list.  Page list
                                   35805             =*  entries follow this pointer.
                                   35806             =*
                                   35807             =*  Each entry consists of 2 fullwords
                                   35808             =*  Word 1 contains a guest real page addr
                                   35809             =*  Word 2 contains a Hiperspace block #
                                   35810             =*
                                   35811             =*  Upon return hi-order byte of Word 2 contains
                                   35812             =*  error info from MVPG or HSPSERV if #HSPRC is
                                   35813             =*  non-zero.
                                   35814             =*
 000000                00000 0000C 35815             =#HSPL    RECORD BEGIN
 000000                            35823  1          =#HSPLNXT   DS     F                      Pointer to next list
 000004                            35824  1          =#HSPLPGE   DS     F                      Page Entry
 000008                            35825  1          =#HSPLBLK   DS     F                      Block Number
                                   35826  1          =#HSPLEND   EQU *

 000008 00                         35828  1          =#HSPLFLG   FLAG   ,
 #HSPLFLG.#HSPLERR 80 ONES         35832  1          =           FLAG   #HSPLERR               HSPACE error
 000009                00009 0000C 35837             =         END    ,

0                                  37243    3875.     *
                                   37244    3876.     *  THIS ROUTINE INITIALIZES THE HIPERSPACE.  THE GUEST CALLER CAN
                                   37245    3877.     *  INVOKE THIS ROUTINE DIRECTLY BUT IN SIMULATION MODE THIS CODE
                                   37246    3878.     *  IS DEFERRED UNTIL THE FIRST I/O REQUEST IS RECEIVED TO ENSURE
                                   37247    3879.     *  THAT THE PAGE/SWAP DATA SET OPEN HAS COMPLETED AND THAT DDBBLKCT
                                   37248    3880.     *  HAS BEEN UPDATED.  THIS VALUE MAY BE OBTAINED FROM THE DSCB OF
                                   37249    3881.     *  A REAL PAGE DATA SET AND IS USED TO DETERMINE THE MAXIMUM SIZE OF
                                   37250    3882.     *  THE HIPERSPACE BEING OPENED WHEN IN SIMULATION MODE.  ON A
                                   37251    3883.     *  DIRECT INVOCATION, THE VALUE IS GIVEN IN #HSPSIZE BY THE CALLER.
                                   37252    3884.     *

0                                  39159    4115.     *******************************************************************
                                   39160    4116.     *                                                                 *
                                   39161    4117.     *    HSRDWRT - Common Hiperspace Read/Write routine               *
                                   39162    4118.     *                                                                 *
                                   39163    4119.     *                                                                 *
                                   39164    4120.     *    Input - @HSRDWRT                                             *
                                   39165    4121.     *                                                                 *
                                   39166    4122.     *******************************************************************
-
                                   39168    4124.     *
                                   39169    4125.     *  THIS ROUTINE PERFORMS PAGE MOVEMENT BETWEEN CENTRAL STORAGE
                                   39170    4126.     *  AND HIPERSPACE EXPANDED STORAGE.  HIPERSPACE CAN BE EITHER
                                   39171    4127.     *  STANDARD OR EXPANDED STORAGE ONLY (ESO).  STANDARD HSPACE
                                   39172    4128.     *  WILL BE PAGED OUT TO AUXILIARY STORAGE WHEN MVS RSM DETECTS
                                   39173    4129.     *  A SHORTAGE OF EXPANDED STORAGE, THUS ITS DATA INTEGRITY IS
                                   39174    4130.     *  ALWAYS ASSURED.  AN ESO HSPACE ACTS ONLY AS A CACHE AND
                                   39175    4131.     *  THE USER IS EXPECTED TO KEEP A COPY OF THE DATA ELSEWHERE
                                   39176    4132.     *  BECAUSE IF DATA IN ESO IS DISCARDED BY RSM IT CAN NEVER BE
                                   39177    4133.     *  RETRIEVED FROM ESTOR UNTIL IT IS WRITTEN ONCE AGAIN INTO
                                   39178    4134.     *  HIPERSPACE.
                                   39179    4135.     *
                                   39180    4136.     *  PAGE MOVEMENT IS FIRST ATTEMPTED WITH A DIRECT MVPG INSTRUCTION.
                                   39181    4137.     *  A DIRECT MVPG SUCCEEDS ONLY WHEN BOTH A CENTRAL AND EXTENDED
                                   39182    4138.     *  STORAGE FRAME CURRENTLY BACK UP THE VIRTUAL PAGE AND HIPERSPACE
                                   39183    4139.     *  BLOCK MVPG OPERANDS.  THUS, A MVPG WRITE TO A HIPERSPACE BLOCK
                                   39184    4140.     *  WILL FAIL UNTIL AN HSPSERV WRITE HAS BEEN PERFORMED TO ASSIGN AN
                                   39185    4141.     *  ESTOR FRAME FOR THE BLOCK.  LIKEWISE, A MVPG READ FROM A
                                   39186    4142.     *  PAGED-OUT HIPERSPACE BLOCK WILL ALSO FAIL. IN THESE CASES EXCEPT
                                   39187    4143.     *  FOR A DISCARDED ESO PAGE, THE OPERATION MUST BE RETRIED WITH AN
                                   39188    4144.     *  HSPSERV REQUEST IN ORDER TO ASSIGN AN ESTOR FRAME TO A NEW BLOCK
                                   39189    4145.     *  OR RECALL A PAGED-OUT FRAME.
                                   39190    4146.     *
                                   39191    4147.     *  ALTHOUGH IT IS NOT MENTIONED IN THE IBM MANUALS, A CENTRAL
                                   39192    4148.     *  STORAGE FRAME TO BE USED IN A MVPG OR HSPSERV OPERATION MAY NOT
                                   39193    4149.     *  BE PAGE-FIXED.  THUS ORVYL PAGES MAY NOT BE DIRECTLY USED IN A
                                   39194    4150.     *  MVPG OR HSPSERV OPERATION. OTHERWISE A CONDITION CODE OF 1 OR AN
                                   39195    4151.     *  01D ABEND WITH REASON CODE XXXX10XX WILL RESULT.  THE FOLLOWING
                                   39196    4152.     *  HIPERSPACE ROUTINES WILL USE A STORAGE MACRO TO OBTAIN STORAGE
                                   39197    4153.     *  FOR A PAGE BUFFER.
                                   39198    4154.     *
1IOSERV   (IOSE00) (09:40) (22MAR04) ORVYL'S ESO Hiperspace Service Routines                                                Page  185

                                   40273  1 4433.     *  SUBTASK TO DO THIS FOR US ASYNCHRONOUSLY.  A CODE OF ZERO
                                   40274  1 4434.     *  IS RETURNED TO THE REQUESTOR INDICATING THAT THE REQUEST

                                   42907  1 4902.     *        buffer control block field in the DCB it will, in fact,

0                                  43334    5027.     *******************************************************************
                                   43335    5028.     *                                                                 *
                                   43336    5029.     *   HSPCETSK - HIPERSPACE WAIT service                            *
                                   43337    5030.     *                                                                 *
                                   43338    5031.     *  THIS TASK IS ONLY REQUIRED FOR STANDARD HIPERSPACE REQUESTS    *
                                   43339    5032.     *  WHICH CAN NECESSITATE I/O TO DASD FOR PAGED-OUT FRAMES AND     *
                                   43340    5033.     *  AND WILL COMPLETE ASYNCHRONOUOSLY.  THIS REQUEST IS STARTED    *
                                   43341    5034.     *  IN A SUBTASK SO THAT THE MOTHER TASK WILL NOT BE PUT TO SLEEP  *
                                   43342    5035.     *  WAITING FOR THE I/O TO COMPLETE.  ESO HIPERSPACES DO NOT       *
                                   43343    5036.     *  INVOLVE I/O TO DASD HENCE WILL ALWAYS COMPLETELY SYNCHRONOUSLY *
                                   43344    5037.     *  IN THE MAIN TASK, ALONG WITH STANDARD HIPERSPACE WRITES.       *
                                   43345    5038.     *                                                                 *
                                   43346    5039.     *     Input -  SBTPARM                                            *
                                   43347    5040.     *                                                                 *
                                   43348    5041.     *    Output -                                                     *
                                   43349    5042.     *                                                                 *
                                   43350    5043.     *                                                                 *
                                   43351    5044.     *******************************************************************
-

0                                  44609  2 5253.     *
                                   44610  2 5254.     *  THE FOLLOWING CODE MAKES SURE THAT WE DO NOT SIGNAL MODULE
                                   44611  2 5255.     *  GSTINTF TO DO I/O BACK-END PROCESSING UNTIL WE ARE NOTIFIED
                                   44612  2 5256.     *  THAT THE ORIGINAL FRONT-END PROCESSING STARTED BY SSCH HAS
                                   44613  2 5257.     *  ENDED.  OTHERWISE, DUE TO MULTIPROCESSING EFFECTS WHICH WILL
                                   44614  2 5258.     *  NOT HAPPEN WITH REAL PAGE OR SWAP I/O, THE GUEST MACHINE CAN
                                   44615  2 5259.     *  BE POSTED FOR THE I/O INTERRUPT BEFORE IT GETS CONTROL FROM
                                   44616  2 5260.     *  THE SSCH.  WE WILL TRY TO AVOID THIS IF POSSIBLE BY INTRODUCING
                                   44617  2 5261.     *  AN STIMERM DELAY.
                                   44618  2 5262.     *
 0042A4 5820 8014            00014 44619  2 5263.                  L     RA,HSRWRQID
                                   44620  2 5264.     *
                                   44621  2 5265.     *  IRCBHSP IS TURNED ON IN ROUTINE HSRDWRT BEFORE OUR SUBTASK WAS
                                   44622  2 5266.     *  AWAKENED.  WHEN HSRDWRT RETURNS TO THE CALLER (GSTINTF ROUTINE
                                   44623  2 5267.     *  IXSSCH), GSTINTF TURNS IT  OFF.  IF WE ARE DISPATCHED BEFORE
                                   44624  2 5268.     *  THIS HAPPENS, WE WILL TRY TO DEFER SIGNALLING GSTINTF BACK-END.
                                   44625  2 5269.     *
 USING  IRCB,R2                    44626  2 5270.                  WITH  (IRCB,RA),'NC IRCBHSP,IRCBHSP'

                                   44662  3 5273.     *  WE WAIT FOR A MINIMUM INTERVAL.
                                   44663  3 5274.     *

 USING  IRCB,R2
